race.comment: Time for the 2YOs now, where ACE QUEEN SUITED (9) has trialled very well coming in. She's a half-sibling to two winners and she showed good adaptability there when sitting off the speed in her heat. Speed looks strong in this so it should suit her pattern and a forward showing is expected on debut. PROPERATA (7) led in that same trial and while tiring late, wasn't beaten all that far. He can sit handy from the draw and Chris Parnham riding is a good push for his chance. Should be fit enough after two trials and he can give a sight. CALL TO ORDER (10) ran them off their feet in a 400m heat at Belmont a couple of weeks ago. Tricky barrier, but her speed was a highlight and she's worth keeping an eye on in betting. PARMALEE (11) trialled well coming in and the Wolfe stable have engaged their strike man in McGruddy for her debut. Keep safe. LUCY RED (8) looks the best of the raced brigade.
